de.deaod.jstormlib.utility

Class ArrayDataReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • java.io.ByteArrayInputStream
        • de.deaod.jstormlib.utility.ArrayDataReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class ArrayDataReader
extends java.io.ByteArrayInputStream
    This class extends ByteArrayInputStream with the capability to read integer values from a byte array.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Deaod
    See Also:
    ByteArrayInputStream

    • Constructor Detail

      • ArrayDataReader

        public ArrayDataReader(byte[] buf)
        Creates an ArrayDataReader so that it uses buf as its buffer array. The buffer array is not copied. The initial value of pos is 0 and the initial value of count is the length of buf.
        Parameters:
        buf - the input buffer.
        See Also:
        ByteArrayInputStream

      • ArrayDataReader

        public ArrayDataReader(byte[] buf,
               int offset,
               int length)
        Creates ByteArrayInputStream that uses buf as its buffer array. The initial value of pos is offset and the initial value of count is the minimum of offset+length and buf.length. The buffer array is not copied. The buffer's mark is set to the specified offset.
        Parameters:
        buf - the input buffer.
        offset - the offset in the buffer of the first byte to read.
        length - the maximum number of bytes to read from the buffer.
        See Also:
        ByteArrayInputStream

      • ArrayDataReader

        public ArrayDataReader(byte[] buf,
               java.nio.ByteOrder byteOrder)
        Creates an ArrayDataReader so that it uses buf as its buffer array. The buffer array is not copied. The initial value of pos is 0 and the initial value of count is the length of buf.
        Parameters:
        buf - the input buffer.
        byteOrder - the default byte order with which to read from the array.
        See Also:
        ByteArrayInputStream

      • ArrayDataReader

        public ArrayDataReader(byte[] buf,
               int offset,
               int length,
               java.nio.ByteOrder byteOrder)
        Creates ByteArrayInputStream that uses buf as its buffer array. The initial value of pos is offset and the initial value of count is the minimum of offset+length and buf.length. The buffer array is not copied. The buffer's mark is set to the specified offset.
        Parameters:
        buf - the input buffer.
        offset - the offset in the buffer of the first byte to read.
        length - the maximum number of bytes to read from the buffer.
        byteOrder - the default byte order with which to read from the array.
        See Also:
        ByteArrayInputStream
